                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Living in a place where everything is nearby is all you need. In this regard, the Kincora neighbourhood doesn't disappoint you. There are a good number of shopping centres near Kincora and two of the prominent ones are Beacon Hill and Creekside Shopping Centre.</p>
                    <p>Creekside Shopping Centre is just outside the Kincora neighbourhood and is within walking distance from the community. The shopping centre spans approximately 40.8 acres and is home to different retail shops, including medical stores, grocery shops, home improvement stores, restaurants, financial institutions, and health and fitness facilities.</p>
                    <p>Beacon Hill Shopping Mall includes major brands like Costco, The Brick, Winners, Home Depot, Canadian Tire, and more.</p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Parks are an integral part of a neighbourhood. Community parks provide many benefits to the residents. They provide a serene environment where people can relax and de-stress from the daily grind. Kids can unwind by playing various sports. Health enthusiasts can be fit by performing yoga, meditation, and other physical exercises in nature. People can gather and socialize at the park in the evenings, which improves their communication skills. In addition to this, the trees, flowers, and plants in the park contribute to the clean air.</p>
                    <p>Fortunately, Kincora residents have access to Sallamie Park a huge green space running through the heart of the community. With walking paths, natural grasslands and playgrounds dotting this green space there is plenty for residents to explore. Pathways even lead from the park to other natural areas in the city so you can easily explore your neighbouring communities as well. </p>
                    <p>On the other hand, if you are looking for a park with numerous recreational activities, then Symons Valley Park won't disappoint you. Located south of Sage Hill Crossing, residents of all five communities, i.e. Sage Hill, Kincora, Sherwood, Evanston, and Hidden Valley, can access the park. The park is in its initial planning stage and the construction will kick start in the year 2023. Once the park is operational, you can take advantage of different recreational activities. The plan includes tennis courts, an amphitheatre, cycling tracks, playgrounds, and BBQ and picnic areas for families to enjoy.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
